node.text:
Ahhhhh I am sooo excited to finally share this with you!!

Although we had initially planned this to look a little different pre-COVID, we were determined to make it happen one way or another!!

I want to give back to YOU and truly show you what YOU have taught me about loving myself, being comfortable in my own skin and BEING confident!

HOW TO WIN🔥
❤️post a photo or video of you feeling your most confident!
❤️hashtag #actconfidentchallenge and tag @sarahs_day and @whitefoxboutique 
❤️WORLDWIDE entires accepted! Challenge closes on the 14th of Feb

🥰be confident, have fun with it and EMBRACE YOU!!!

THIS TASTES LIKE PINK/RED LOLLIES!! If you’re like me and go straight for the red jelly beans and gummies before yellow, orange and green then THIS is the smoothie bowl for you!!

🍌1/2 banana
🍓1 cup frozen strawberry
🍍1/2 cup frozen pineapple
🥛1/4 cup oat milk
💪🏼1 tsp @tropeaka vanilla lean protein
🌸1 tsp body bloom @tropeaka 
🌺1 tsp pink pataya powder @tropeaka 

Top with fresh fruit, coconut and hemp seeds!! ENJOY!

P.S if you want to save 15% on @tropeaka use code SEZZY15 
#tropeakaambassador

node.text:
TIDY WITH ME!!

Going into our fourth week of lockdown I found myself really down, unmotivated, negative and honestly…sad. I decided to put my mental health and self thoughts FIRST today! I woke up, did my first workout in over a week and tidied the whole house. I can’t begin to tell you the impact that a clean space has on my mindset and mood🥰👏🏼

node.text:
Bringing in week 4 of Sydney lockdown with an afternoon hemp and banana smoothie🍌
Kurt and I have been finding ourselves snacking soooo much more than usual!

Today I’ve made a conscious effort to be more mindful with my eating and not just sit around, snacking because I’m bored. 

I usually have my protein smoothies around 3pm as that’s when I get peckish and have a little sugar craving🥰

🍌1 banana
🍌oat milk
🍌cookie dough fit protein @tropeaka 
🍌hemp seeds
🍌cashew butter
+ ice 

DELICIOUS!!!

node.text:
Balancing business, fitness, Foxy, Abby and everything in between during LOCKDOWN week 3!!

Today Foxy woke up after a huuuuge 20 minute nap😳(sense my sarcasm there?)
An over-tired toddler mixed with a mummy trying to workout in the backyard never goes to well…

Kurt and I have been dealing with this lockdown but doing a lot of half days each. We tag team around 1pm and the other is able to work. So today, Kurt could see i mentally really needed to move my body so he smashed out a little 15 minute boxing burner with me before I hit the laptop and he took over toddler duties. 

Here’s a fun little combo we made up today!
